items.comment: A specialization of AttackSubmarine. Each instance of LosAngelesClassSubmarine is an attack submarine built for the U.S. Navy.

label: litchi tree
LycheeTree
items.comment: A tree bearing oval fruit with a hard scaly outer covering, small hard seed, and edible flesh that surrounds the seed.

items.subClassOf: support given by one agent to another
label: logistics support
LogisticsSupport

items.comment: A specialization of both FuelPoweredDevice and SelfPoweredDevice. Each instance of InternalCombustionPoweredDevice is a device powered by an internal combustion engine. Specializations of InternalCombustionPoweredDevice include Motorboat and RoadVehicle_InternalCombustionEngine.
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: device powered by an internal combustion engine
devices powered by an internal combustion engine
label: internal combustion powered device
InternalCombustionPoweredDevice
insulated wire
InsulatedWire
items.comment: The collection of all insulated wires. A type of ElectricalWire and LayeredObject. InsulatedWire is an ArtifactTypeByGenericCategory.

label: type of leaf classified by structure
LeafTypeByStructure
items.Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: types of leaf classified by structure
items.comment: The collection of leaf types by structure: SimpleLeaf, CompoundLeaf, DoublyCompoundLeaf.

label: type of list by member type
ListTypeByMemberType
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: type of list classified by member type
types of list by member type
types of list classified by member type
items.comment: A collection of collections. Each element of ListTypeByMemberType is a collection of lists of objects of a specified type. For example, (ListOfTypeFn City), the collection of lists of cities, is a member of ListTypeByMemberType. Another instance would be (ListOfTypeFn Integer), the collection of lists of integers.

A Law is a miniature GovernmentCOC that expresses a legal requirement or restriction. For instance, one Law might say, effectively, that bigamy is illegal. A Law is declared to be part of a LegalCode by using subWorks. Note that one Law can be part of more than one LegalCode.
label: law
Law
lexicon slice microtheory
LexiconSliceMicrotheory
items.comment: A LexiconSliceMicrotheory is a kind of LexicalDataMicrotheory that includes only selected content from a particular lexicon or set of lexicons.

The collection of all appeals of decisions handed down by judicial bodies by the party that was maleficiary of the decision. Such appeals are made to appellate courts [AppealsCourt], which may reject or hear the appeal. A decision of an appeals court can be appealed to a "higher" appeals court. A legal appeal is normally part of the case that started in the court of initial jurisdiction.
label: legal appeal
LegalAppeal
lemon zester
LemonZester
items.comment: A specialization of FoodOrDrinkPreparationDevice. Lemon zesters are used to remove lemon zest from lemon skins.

label: KMS
KnowledgeManagementProgram
items.comment: The collection of all instances of Knowledge Management Software: software that gets the right knowledge sources (including documents and references to web pages and human experts) to the right person at the right time.  The definition of this is nebulous and controversial, but it includes at least all pieces of software which are (a.) marketed as 'Knowledge Management Software', and (b.) used to steer relevant documents to the people that need them.  Includes information retrieval software based on subject relevance metadata.

label: leguminous plant
Legume-ThePlant
items.comment: The collection of all leguminous plants. A type of CropPlant and TerrestrialOrganism. Legume_ThePlant is a BiologicalFamily and a SpatiallyDisjointObjectType.

label: the Joint Surveillance and Target Attack Radar System
JSTARS-RADAR
items.comment: JSTARS, or "Joint Surveillance Target Attack Radar System," is an air-to-surface surveillance system designed to locate, classify and track ground targets in all weather conditions.  While flying in friendly airspace, the joint Army-Air Force program can look deep behind hostile borders to detect and track ground movements in both forward and rear areas. It has a range of more than 150 miles (250 km). These capabilities make Joint STARS effective for dealing with any contingency, whether actual or impending military aggression, international treaty verification, or border violation.

subClassOf: keeping something in a certain state
label: keeping an animal awake
KeepingAnAnimalAwake
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: will have kept an animal awake
items.comment: A FirstOrderCollection and specialization of KeepingInACertainState. Each instance of KeepingAnAnimalAwake is an event in which something (e.g. a loud noise, excessive Caffeine, Fear) keeps an animal from GoingToSleep.
A PersonTypeByOccupation. Each instance of Lumberjack is a person who makes his living by cutting down trees and/or cutting fallen trees into logs.
label: lumberjack
Lumberjack
jersey island person
JerseyIslandPerson
items.comment: This is the collection of people who are citizens of Jersey_Island, or participate in its NationalCulture.

label: interposed covering
InterposedCovering
items.comment: The collection of coverings which cover an object by virtue of being interposed between the object and its environment

label: killing by organism unique
KillingByOrganism-Unique
items.comment: A specialization of both PhysicalDestructionEvent and KillingByOrganism. Each instance of KillingByOrganism_Unique consists of one living organism ending (either intentionally or unintentionally) the life of one other living organism. Events of this type start sometime prior to the death of the individual (We leave it open whether, in some cases, some of the events leading up the the death of the individual are part of the killing event) and ends at the last moment of the individual's death.

label: laurel
LaurelBush
items.comment: The collection of all laurel bushes. A type of LaurelOrder, EvergreenPlant, and Bush. The collection LaurelBush is an OrganismClassificationType and a SpatiallyDisjointObjectType.

label: device powered by kinetic energy
KineticEnergyPoweredDevice
items.comment: A specialization of PoweredDevice. Each instance of KineticEnergyPoweredDevice does not have any "on-board" energy source incorporated into it, at least not one supplying the bulk of the power requirements of the device. Instead, its operating power is supplied by the kinetic energy from something else in motion -- such as animal muscle power (including human labor), wind energy, or hydraulic power. Specializations of this collection include Pulley and Piano_Acoustic. (Cf. SelfPoweredDevice, which includes, e.g., electric organs.)

label: KB content regression test
KBContentRegressionTest
items.type: type of specification for a CycL query and its expected results
items.comment: A subcollection of <font color="#ff0000">#$KBContentTest-FullySpecified</font> which are all expected to succeed, and for which it is considered an error if they begin to fail.

label: looking puzzled
LookingPuzzled
items.comment: The subset of making facial expressions in which an agent appears confused or hesitant about something; the signals may be subtle and vary, including eyebrows either raised or contracted in a slight frown.
A legal event
label: legal proceeding
LegalProceeding
learning a skill
LearningASkill
items.comment: This is the subcollection of Learning containing those events in which the performer learns some new skill.

items.label: Kamakahala
items.comment: The collection of all Kamakahala. A type of FloweringPlant. Kamakahala is an Endangered_OrganismTypeByExistentialThreatLevel, a SpatiallyDisjointObjectType, and a BiologicalSpecies.

label: Leisure Products
LeisureProducts-SubIndustrySP
items.comment: The 'Leisure Products' sub-industry, as defined by Standard and Poor's.

label: instant messaging
InstantMessaging
items.comment: A specialization of InternetCommunication in which text messages are sent more-or-less directly and in real-time (cf. EMailCommunication) over the internet. Typically, both parties in an instant-messaging conversation see each line of text right after it is typed, thus making it more like a telephone conversation than exchanging letters.

label: nursing home
LongTermMedicalCareProvidingOrganization
items.comment: The collection of all Organizations that provide long-term medical care for patients.

label: anomalous systemic vein and superior vena cava ligation
LigationAnomalousSystemicVeinsSuperiorVenaCava-SurgicalProcedure
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: anomalous systemic vein and superior vena cava ligations
ligation of anomalous systemic veins and superior vena cava
ligations of anomalous systemic veins and superior vena cava

label: interdicting bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
InterdictingFireRoute7Bridge-TaskedAction
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: had interdicted bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
has interdicted bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
have interdicted bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
interdict bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
interdicted bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
interdicts bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
will have interdicted bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT
will interdict bridge Fire Route 7 in COLT

items.subClassOf: loan agreement type by term option
label: loan agreement type by term duration
LoanAgreementTypeByTermDuration
items.comment: A specialization of LoanAgreementTypeByTermOption. Instances are types of loans, defined as having a common term duration (e.g., 30 years, 15 years, etc.) in common. See also loanTermDuration.

label: leather jacket
LeatherJacket
items.comment: The collection of jackets made primarily of leather.

label: intelligence official
IntelligenceOfficial
items.comment: The collection of all 'official' members of an GovernmentIntelligenceOrganization: i.e., IntelligenceAgents who are also PublicOfficials in the government of which their GovernmentIntelligenceOrganization is a part.

label: KFD internal KR term
KFDInternalKRTerm
items.comment: The collection of Cyc terms used internally by Cyc to reason about the UIA knowledge entry process. Only UIA-specific terms should be made instances of this collection -- terms relevant to KR and KE processes in general do not belong in this collection.

label: posture with legs crossed on some piece of furniture
LegsCrossedOnFurniture
items.Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: postures with legs crossed on some piece of furniture
items.comment: The posture of sitting with one's legs crossed at some point on some furniture - like a table or desk.

label: locking
LockingSomething
items.comment: An instance of TemporalObjectType and a specialization of ChangingDeviceState. Each instance of LockingSomething is an action which changes the state of some lockable device from Device_Unlocked to Device_Locked.
The collection of insects which can give a person a medical condition known as 'head lice' (see HeadLice_Condition). Having such an condition is usually associated with poor hygiene.
label: louse
Louse
jelly
Jelly-Foodstuff
items.comment:
This is the collection of all instances of jelly. Jelly is generally made
from fruit, which is combined with sugar and cooked until a certain temperature
is reached. Sometimes pectin is added to aid in gelling. Jelly is then
strained so that it is clear.

label: international postal code
InternationalPostalCode
items.comment: The collection of all international postal codes. A type of PostalCode. The concept InternationalPostalCode is a UniqueIDType and an IDStringType.

label: insecure mail list administration pages fault
InsecureMailListAdministrationPagesFault
items.Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: insecure mail list administration pages faults
items.comment: A program has  this fault if a specially-formed input  to that program will allow access to the list administration pages to an  unauthorized user.
Lotion is a collection of lotions. Lotions are opaque, fluid, tangible stuff applied externally on the skin. Lotions are less viscous than creams.
label: lotion
Lotion
land vehicle
LandTransportationVehicle
items.comment: A specialization of LandTransportationDevice and TransportationDevice_Vehicle. Each instance of LandTransportationVehicle is a device which is both self-powered and controlled in some fashion by a user, and is used for transportation across land. Specializations of LandTransportationVehicle include the collections Automobile, Snowmobile, Truck, and Bus_RoadVehicle, but not collections of non-SelfPoweredDevices such as Bicycle or Skateboard.
LogicBomb is the collection of MaliciousComputerPrograms designed to activate under some, specified circumstances. If activation is determined by time then see TimeBomb_Computer.
label: logic bomb
LogicBomb
irregular maneuver formation
Irregular-ManeuverFormation
items.comment: This attribute applies to units which are moving in an irregularly-shaped, hard-to-describe formation, rather than a line or column formation.

label: degree of fame
LevelOfRenown
items.comment: Level of awareness about something.  Higher values indicate knowing more and more about various aspects of it.
The collection of Underwear that typically cover all of the body except the head and neck, hands, and feet. They are worn under the clothes for warmth.
label: long underwear
LongUnderwear
Leptospira Genus
Leptospira-Genus
items.comment: These ProkaryoticCells are tightly coiled, thin, flexible spirochetes. These are oxidase-positive as well as catalase- and/or peroxidase-positive Bacterium.

label: introduction of someone
IntroducingSomeone
items.comment: A specialization of SocialOccurrence. Instances of this collection are events in which someone is explicitly (but not necessarily formally) introduced to someone else.. In an event of this sort, it is presumed (prehaps incorrectly) that the introduced agents not familiar with (cf. acquaintedWith and mutualAcquaintances) each other.

label: iteration attribute
IterationEventByType
items.comment: A collection of collections. Instances of this collection are collections of IterativeEvents of a similar type understood in the most general way -- example: 'stepwise', 'one at a time' -- or units of specified object types -- example: (IterationTypeFn StepOfStairs), which would be used to describe the iteration of a motion up the stairs one step at a time.

subClassOf: type of loan agreement classified by feature
label: type of loan agreement classified by principal feature
LoanAgreementTypeByConformityToAmountLimits
items.Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: types of loan agreement classified by principal feature
items.comment: A collection of collections. Each instance of LoanAgreementTypeByConformityToAmountLimits is a collection of LoanAgreements that share a certain status due to the amounts of their principles relative to (maximum or minimum) lending amount limits their creditors have for similar loans. See for example the instances JumboLoan and FloorLimitLoan.

label: interval that is bounded at the bottom
Interval-BoundedBelow
items.Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: intervals that is bounded at the bottom
items.disjointWith: interval that is unbounded at the bottom
items.comment: A specialization of ScalarInterval. Each instance of Interval_BoundedBelow is an interval that has a lower bound. Example: the interval comprising all integers greater than 10.

label: letter PIT
Letter-PIT
items.comment: The collection of all mts which represent the content of letters (personal letters, business letters, etc.).

label: keld
Keld
items.comment: A specialization of BodyOfWater. Kelds are deep, relatively still areas in Rivers.

label: juice concentrate
JuiceConcentrate
items.comment: Juice from which much of the water has been extracted (how?). Frozen juice concentrate is a common consumer product.  Juice concentrates are also used in manufacturing juice drinks and blends.

label: islamic month type
IslamicMonthType
items.comment: A collection of Collections. Instances of IslamicMonthType are the canonical subsets of IslamicMonth in the IslamicLunarCalendar system.

label: library loan agreement
LibraryLoanAgreement
items.comment: A specialization of LoanAgreement. In each instance of LibraryLoanAgreement, a member of Library_Organization borrows (see BorrowingLibraryItem) some Library_Organization items. The borrower agrees to return (see ReturningLibraryItem) the borrowed library-items within the stipulated loanTermDuration. There may be options of RenewingLibraryItem also.

label: left bundle branch anterior fascicle
LeftBundleBranchAnteriorFascicle
items.comment: The LeftBundleBranch includes two fascicles of Purkinje fibers that enervates a large number of myocytes in the Myocardium: the LeftBundleBranchAnteriorFascicle and the LeftBundleBranchPosteriorFascicle.
The collection of all labia minora. An instance of LabiaMinora is one of a pair of folds of fatty tissue located just inside the LabiaMajora that enclose the openings of the Urethra and Vagina.
label: labium minus
LabiaMinora
type of island
IslandRegionTypeByPlurality
items.comment: A collection of collections. Each instance of IslandRegionTypeByPlurality is a specialization of IslandRegion whose instances all consist of the same "plurality" of whole Islands, where that might be either none, one, or more-than-one.

label: knowledge acquisition goal verifying induction
KnowledgeAcquisitionGoal-VerifyingInduction
items.comment: The goal-category of verifying knowledge formed via induction.

label: interaction guiding predicate
Interaction-GuidingPredicate
items.comment: This is the collection of CycL Predicates whose main intended purpose is to register information about the state of Cyc in the course of an interaction. This information can then be used by Cyc to guide its own behavior. Assertions involving these predicates will depend upon the current state of the KB and hence these predicates should be notAssertible, but they are not, since currently this makes it impossible to conclude clauses employing such predicates via forward rules and hence makes it impossible for Cyc to reason about it's current state.

label: lawn and garden product
LawnAndGardenMarketCategory
items.comment: The category of lawn and garden supplies.  This includes items like garden hoses and lawn furniture, and may also include stuff such as garden fertilizer, seeds, and plants
The process of making payments in order to bring the balance towards 0.
items.Mx4rvjldVJwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: loan repaying type by repayment plan type
label: repayment
LoanRepaying

items.comment: Pb(NO3)2, a specialization of InorganicCompound. Instances are composed of one atom of Lead and two molecules of nitrogen trioxide (NO3).
label: lead nitrate
LeadNitrate
investing in a hedge fund
InvestingInAHedgeFund
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: had invested in a hedge fund
has invested in a hedge fund
have invested in a hedge fund
will have invested in a hedge fund
will invest in a hedge fund
items.comment: A specialization of Investing. Each instance of InvestingInAHedgeFund is a complex event in which a wealthy investor buys into a hedge fund (see HedgeFund), and the fund manager uses (typically high-risk, high-payoff) strategies to grow the fund. Hedge fund managers usually have the prospect of profit due to a high commission rate as motivation for performance.

label: iranian justice minister
IranianJusticeMinister
items.comment:
A specialization of Minister_Governmental and IranianPerson. An IranianJusticeMinister is the member of the IranianCabinet whose job is to advise the president on matters involving the judicial system.

Cf. IranianHeadOfJudiciary.
The collection of all lunatics. A type of HomoSapiens.
label: lunatic
Lunatic
lepidolite
Lepidolite
items.comment: The collection of all lepidolite. A type of Mineral. Lepidolite is an ExistingStuffType.

A specialization of PhysiologicalCondition. Each instance of this collection is a condition that arise when a mammal is unable to sleep adequately over a prolonged period of time. See also SleepDeprivation.
label: insomniac
Insomnia
interest accrual type by account type
InterestAccrualTypeByAccountType
items.comment: An instance of FacetingCollectionType and SiblingDisjointCollectionType. Instances are specializations of AccruingInterest, each instance of which involves increasing the balance (see accountBalance), through the charging or crediting of interest to a common type of account. Notable instances include AccruingInterestOnASavingsAccount and AccruingInterestOnALoan.
The collection of all kingfishers. A type of Bird. Kingfisher is a BiologicalTaxon.
label: kingfisher
Kingfisher
irrigation system
IrrigationSystem
items.comment: A specialization of PathArtifactSystem. Each instance of IrrigationSystem is a network of irrigation ditches, and also contains either a reservoir, canal, pump, well, or drain.
The collection of instances of Truck designed to transport livestock from place to place.
label: livestock carrier
LivestockCarrier
police department
LocalPoliceOrganization
items.type: law enforcement organization type by jurisdiction
items.comment: A collection of law enforcement organizations. An element of LocalPoliceOrganization is a local police department, not state or national police organizations.

label: looking upward
LookingUpward
items.comment: A specialization of WatchingSomething. Each instance of LookingUpward is an event in which a perceptual agent directs its visual sensors upward.

label: listening to voicemail
ListeningToVoiceMail
items.comment: The collection of all listening to voicemail. A type of ListeningOnATelephone.

label: interval that is unbounded at the bottom
Interval-UnboundedBelow
items.Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: intervals that is unbounded at the bottom
items.comment: A subcollection of ScalarIntervals that is not bounded at the bottom. It is disjoint with Interval_BoundedBelow.

label: intravenous infusion
IntravenousInfusionProcess
items.comment: The process of introducing a solution into an animal's vein by means of a container connected to a needle by a flexible tube.

label: italicized character
ItalicizedCharacter
items.comment: An instance of FontTypeByStyle. Instances are individual instances of Character_Abstract that appear as italicized text.

label: leaf epidermis
LeafEpidermis
items.comment: The outer-most cell layer of angiosperm leaves.

The collection of all straight lines combined with an associated intrinsic direction. Line_Straight_Directed is not a specialization of Line_Straight, since only one Line_Straight can pass through a given point and be parallel to another line in a Euclidean space. Two instances of Line_Straight_Directed have this property.
label: directed straight line
Line-Straight-Directed

items.comment: A collection of small to medium-sized dogs.
label: Italian greyhound
ItalianGreyhound
Minister of Petroleum
IranianOilMinister
items.comment: A specialization of Minister_Governmental and IranianPerson. An IranianOilMinister is the member of the IranianCabinet whose job is to advise the president on matters involving the production and trade of oil.

label: larderellite
Larderellite
items.comment: The collection of all larderellite. A type of Mineral. Larderellite is an ExistingStuffType.

label: jewish gift
JewishGift
items.comment: An instance of GiftTypeByReligion. The collection of all Gifts that are somehow associated with Judaism.

label: the International 1924 spheroid
International1924Spheroid
Mx4rwLSVCpwpEbGdrcN5Y29ycA: oblate spheroid with the inverse flattening 297 that is also an oblate spheroid whose Spheroid Semimajor Axis Length is 6,378,388 meters
items.comment: The International1924Spheroid is the collection of OblateSpheroids with a semi-major axis of length (Meter 6378388) (see spheroidSemimajorAxisLength) and an inverse flattening of 297.0 (see spheroidInverseFlattening).

label: intensive care unit room stay
IntensiveCareUnitRoomStay
items.comment: The collection of events in which a person checks into a hospital, stays in a room in the intensive care ward, and then (usually) checks out again. Each of these is a subEvent of a HospitalCareEvent, which might have other subEvents such as Surgery, administration of medicines, etc.

label: 1 = Left Atrium, 2 = Left Ventricle.
LeftInflow-STS-Transformation
items.comment: The collection of SKSI encoding or decoding evaluation events in which  1 = Left Atrium, 2 = Left Ventricle.

The groupMembers of LineOfObjects are arranged such that inFrontOf_Directly applies of one another. The current (May 96) default is that the objects in the line, are in it for the duration of the existence of the LineOfObjects. If the line is Straight then all objects in the line are either in front of or in back of one another.
label: line of objects
LineOfObjects

items.comment: A collection of events. Each instance of LaserBeam is an event in which a monochromatic rays of light travel in a coherent directional beam.
label: laser beam
LaserBeam

items.comment: The collection of all PropositionalConceptualWorks consisting of a small number of sentences intended primarily to amuse an addressee. Instances of Joke_CW often involve wordplay that depends on the identity of the words used in addition to the propositions expressed. Instances of Joke_CW can be either monologues, in which the speaker relates an instance of Narrative with a humorous ending, or (usually formulaic) dialogues, in which the addressee reponds to the speaker's utterances in a predictable way. Use JokeAboutFn to create specializations of Joke_CW. (See Joke_IBT for actual written or spoken jokes and JokeTelling for acts of telling jokes.)
label: funny stuff
Joke-CW
line replaceable unit
LineReplaceableUnit
items.comment: A specialization of PhysicalDevice. This is the collection of devices considered to be "line replaceable units".

label: keeping
KeepingSomething
items.comment: The collection of events in which some Agent_PartiallyTangible deliberately maintains possession of something.

label: lilliput query open good
LilliputQuery-OpenGood
items.comment: The subcollection of LilliputQuerys that are open and known to be answerable - can generate at least one answer. The queries are answerable removal only, with no new terms allowed.
The collection of all javelins. A type of Spear use in modern throwing competitions. The collection Javelin is an ArtifactTypeByFunction.
label: javelin
Javelin

items.comment: The collection of copies of letters (#$Letter-Missive). These may be InformationBearingObjects on instances of SheetOfPaper or photon patterns being emitted from a CathodeRayTube, for example.
label: letter
LetterCopy
iodide ion
IodideIon
items.comment: A specialization of MonoatomicAnion. Instances of IodideIon are single Iodine atoms with an ElectronicCharge of -1, which means it has gained an electron.

label: jadeite
Jadeite
items.comment: The collection of all jadeite. A type of Mineral. Jadeite is an ExistingStuffType.

label: physical activity level
LevelOfPhysicalActivity
items.comment: A collection of attributes. Instances of LevelOfPhysicalActivity denote the various intensities of physical effort with which agents perform activities. LevelOfPhysicalActivity includes levels of exertion represented by non-atomic terms (NATs) such as (HighAmountFn LevelOfPhysicalActivity), as well as instances such as ExtremePhysicalActivityLevel. All of those intensities are treated as ordered intervals and must be related appropriately; see ScalarInterval for more detail. See also GenericValueFunction, physicalActivityLevel.

A subset of PurposefulAction and ActionOnObject, Intrusion is the collection of actions in which an agent purposefully and illicitly accesses an individual. Objects that can be the foci of instances of Intrusion include only objects that have a levelOfSecurity that is a specialization of the attribute LimitedAccess.
label: intrusion
Intrusion
low rider road vehicle
LowRiderRoadVehicle
items.comment: The collection of RoadVehicles where the RoadVehicleBody is lowered close to the ground, typically leaving only a few inches of clearance.

label: liqueur
Liqueur
items.comment: The collection of all liqueur. A type of Liquor_Drink. Liqueur is an alcoholic beverage with a high sugar content.
The collection of all keratin, a type of fibrous protein that form the structure of horny epidermal tissues such as hair and nails.  Keratin contains sulfur.
label: keratin
Keratin
leap year jewish
LeapYear-Jewish
items.comment: The collection of Jewish CalendarYears which are leap years. Jewish leap years have an additional month, Adar_JewishMonth.

label: insurance policy description
InsurancePolicyDescription
items.comment: A type of <font color="#ff0000">#$TextualDocument-CW</font>.
Type of traditional Japanese clothing, usually full-length or nearly full-length.
label: kimono
Kimono
lateral cord brachial plexus
LateralCord-BrachialPlexus
items.comment: The collection of all lateral cords of the brachial plexus. The lateral cord is formed by the anterior division of the SuperiorTrunk_BrachialPlexus and the anterior division of the MiddleTrunk_BrachialPlexus. Nerves formed from the lateral cord are the SupraScapularNerve, then LateralPectoralNerve, and the MedianNerve.

label: integration of funds during laundering
IntegrationOfFundsDuringLaundering
items.comment: IntegrationOfFundsDuringLaundering is a sub-collection of ChangeOfPropertyHoldings that is associated with MoneyLaundering. Specifically, an event of this sort represents the completion of a successful instance of MoneyLaundering. After having obscured the source of some funds, the performer situates the laundered funds such that they are accessible for future use.

label: Krispy Kreme
KrispyKremeOutlet
items.comment: The collection of instances of Restaurant_Organization that are franchises of the KrispyKremeCorporation. Each instance of this collection is an organization consisting of the group of people who operate a particular Krispy Kreme franchise.

label: petiole
LeafPetiole
items.comment: The stalk of a leaf that connects it to a stem.

label: lexical interpretation agent
LexicalInterpretationAgent
items.comment: The collection of all software agents that engage in lexical interpretation. This could range from simple word lookup schemes to sophisticated morphological parsers.

label: intelligence unit
IntelligenceUnit-MilitarySpecialty
items.comment: The collection of all military units dedicated to gathering and/or analyzing intelligence. A type of MilitaryUnit_NonCombat. The concept IntelligenceUnit_MilitarySpecialty is a MilitaryUnitSpecialtyType and a MilitaryOrganizationConcept.

label: Javascript command execution fault
JavascriptCommandExecutionFault
items.comment: A program has a JavascriptCommandExecutionFault if an unauthorized person can pass Javascript code to a program and have it execute arbitrary commands.

label: light cruiser
LightCruiser
items.comment: The collection of light cruiser ships.

label: insurance claims department
InsuranceClaimsDepartment
items.comment: A DepartmentTypeByFunction and a specialization of FinanceDepartment. Each instance of InsuranceClaimsDepartment consists of employees who settle an organization's insurance claims.

label: lunar round trip
LunarRoundTrip
items.comment: A specialization of SpaceTransportationEvent and Translation_RoundTrip. Each instance of LunarRoundTrip is an event in which a transporter travels from PlanetEarth to the MoonOfEarth and back.

label: jetty
Jetty
items.comment: A specialization of FlowControlDevice. Instances of Jetty are constructions that extend into a body of water from the shoreline, and are intended to direct currents. Applications incluse, but are not limited to, regulating river channels, fixing river mouths, and influencing the effects of tides. They are frequently made of timbers, earth and stone, or concrete. When constructed of earth and stone, jetties are only distinct from Breakwaters in purpose.
A long thin piece of metal, plastic, bone, or stone, useful for cutting.
label: knife
Knife

items.comment: This is the collection of all instances of liquor. Alcoholic beverages are usually divided into beer, wine, and liquor. Liquors are made by a distilling process, although ingredients are generally added after distillation. Liquor_Drink does not include fortified wines, but does include liqueurs. label: Low Earth Orbit

Satellites in LowEarthOrbit circle the Earth with an altitude of 200 - 500 miles. Satellites in Low Earth Orbit are useful for taking clear and detailed images of the Earth's surface. Most WeatherSatellites and EarthRemoteSensingSatellites circle the Earth in Low Earth Orbit. Also, most satellites are originally released into space from a GroundToOrbitVehicle in Low Earth Orbit. From there, their own power sources drive them into their proper orbit.

Each instance of Liquid_StateOfMatter is an object of a single chemical species in the liquid state of matter. Objects in the liquid state of matter are at a temperature and pressure such that the molecules of the matter move freely relative to their neighbors, but are not excited enough to break free. Liquid objects are characterized at the macroscopic level by special qualities of flow, such as being pourable and conforming to whatever container they occupy. Instances of Liquid_StateOfMatter include a quantity of liquid nitrogen, the water component of a gallon of seawater, a lump of mercury at room temperature, and some molten silver about to be poured into a teapot mold. Counterexamples include a gallon of seawater (since it has dissolved minerals) and 190 proof ethanol (since it is 5% water).

intentional mental situation
IntentionalMentalSituation
items.comment:
A specialization of MentalSituation_SingleSubject (q.v.). Each instance of IntentionalMentalSituation is a mental state or event characterized by intentionality: it is "of" or "about" some thing external to itself. Thoughts (see Thinking), acts of perception (see Perceiving), and propositional attitudes (e.g. BelievingThat and DesiringThat) are three common types of intentional mental situations. Thus, a particular act of thinking about the Eiffel Tower, an event of seeing the Eiffel Tower, and a given subject's believing that the Eiffel Tower is in Paris are three intentional mental situations, all having (at least) the EiffelTower as their object.

Any thing whatsoever can in principle be the object of an intentional mental situation: I can think about a given physical object, an event, a relation, an attribute, a proposition, a mental state (my own or another's), a set, a collection, or anything else. (Note that the above mentioned belief about the Eiffel Tower and Paris is arguably not itself about the proposition that the Eiffel Tower is in Paris. But now note that my belief in the content of the sentence preceding this one clearly is, in part, about that proposition.)

Mental situations that are not intentional, and thus not in this collection, include moods, itches, and pain experiences.

Note that, although they are indirectly related (see e.g. PurposefulMentalActivity), the sense of "intentional" described above is not to be confused with its other sense as an antonym of "accidental".

See also IntentionalMentalEvent, IntentionalMentalState, objectOfMentalSituation, and thinksAbout.

A specialization of CommunicationConvention. Each instance of this collection is a generative system of signs for transmitting information. These signs are normally conventional and arbitrary in nature, though the case of body language is a (borderline) exception to this.

The reality of any given language consists in its being interpretable by some community (usually human -- cf. HumanLanguage). This is not quite true of #$ComputerLanguages, however such languages are only possible insofar as some kind of automation of the process of interpretation (by computers) has been effected. In the case of DeadLanguages, the community may not longer exist (although even if no-one can _speak_ such languages any longer, currently-interpretable texts often remain, cf., for example, AtticGreekDialect).

Languages are most often spoken, but not always (cf. SignLanguage). It is also worth noting that not every system of signs is a language; a certain richness of possible expression is required. Thus MorseCode, for example, though a CommunicationConvention, is not an instance of Language. Finally, this collection is not intended to cover the special vocabulary and usages of a scientific, professional or other group, or a characteristic style of speech or writing (e.g. 'Shakespearean language').
